{{more citations needed|date=October 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}} {{Use Australian English|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox company | name = Australian Dairy Foods | logo = Australian Dairy Foods logo.jpg | type = [[Trade magazine]] | foundation = 1942 | founder = Australian Institute of Dairy Factory Managers and Secretaries | location = [[West Melbourne, Victoria]] | area_served = [[Australia]] | industry = [[News media|Media]] | services = News and information for the post-farmgate dairy sector in Australia | owner = [[Dairy Industry Association of Australia]] | key_people = Editor: Irina Fainberg | homepage = [http://www.diaa.asn.au Dairy Industry Association of Australia] }}
'''''Australian Dairy Foods''''' is a [[trade magazine]] for the dairy industry in Australia. It is published bi-monthly by the [[Dairy Industry Association of Australia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=DIAA Dairy Industry Association of Australia|url=http://www.businessworld-magazine.com/business-associations/diaa-dairy-industry-association-of-australia/|accessdate=28 October 2016|work=Business World Magazine|date=28 April 2011}}</ref>
==History and profile== The magazine was first published in 1942 under the name ''Butter Fat & Solids'' by the Australian Institute of Dairy Factory Managers and Secretaries.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Godbold |first1=Norman |title=100 Years of Co-operation |date=1993 |publisher=Dairy Industry Association of Australia |page=27 |url=https://diaa.asn.au/images/stories/member-only-area/diaa-100-years-coop.pdf}}</ref> In 1979, it was expanded and renamed ''Australian Dairy Foods''.
The magazine covers a range of topics - latest news, company profiles, latest equipment, research, industry insights, and more. Its mission is to deliver accurate and relevant information that contributes to its readers’ industry knowledge and expertise.{{Citation needed|date=February 2012}}
The magazine also features the results of DIAA’s National and State dairy product competitions. Innovators from all sectors of the industry are regularly profiled.
In 2008 ''Australian Dairy Foods'' was recognised for the quality of its news coverage at the "2008 Tabbies", an international B2B competition run by the US-based "Trade, Association and Business Publications International" (TABPI).{{Citation needed|date=February 2012}}
